Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe State has directed the Ministry of Youth, Sports and Social Development to open a portal for the collection of the credentials of all unemployed youths in the state. The portal, which will soon be opened online, will capture the information of graduates with OND, HND, BSc, MSc and PhD for employment into the state civil service at the local, state, and the federal levels. The governor’s directive was announced by the commissioner for Information, Home Affairs and Culture, Alhaji Abdullahi Bego. He advised the state’s unemployed youths to get their credentials ready for onward logging and submission as soon as the portal is opened.